              {
                "id": "6dfff723-24df-4968-acc9-e7914194081e",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.530984Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: Shortly after her daughter Ananya was born, Priya discovered a news report about a popular baby formula brand being recalled due to bacterial contamination \u2014 a brand she had almost chosen based on a neighbor's casual recommendation. \u2014 This near-miss hardened her instinct to never delegate high-stakes decisions to others uncritically, fueling her tension between trusting peers and needing to verify everything herself before acting.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.530984Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "d1150bf4-ab47-4d28-8e9b-cd4a59ccbad9",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.531008Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: When furnishing their first owned flat in Powai, Priya outsourced the interior decisions to a designer recommended by a colleague, only to receive poorly fitted cabinetry and mismatched materials that cost an additional \u20b980,000 to correct. \u2014 The experience calcified her low tolerance for delegating quality-sensitive decisions, making her the primary driver of all household and family purchases regardless of the time cost to herself.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.531008Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "7aef101e-b087-4418-9204-bfedf45ff4c6",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.531033Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: During her postgraduate management program, a behavioral finance module demonstrated through classroom simulations how peer-validated decisions consistently outperformed individual hunches in controlled scenarios, leaving a strong impression on her. \u2014 She internalized a structured preference for seeking trusted peer references before committing to significant choices, but only from a tight, curated circle rather than broad social networks \u2014 explaining both her peer trust orientation and her low social orientation score.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:42:27.531033Z"
              }
