          {
            "title": "The Startup Internship That Wasn't",
            "when": "age 26",
            "event": "He joined a Bengaluru fintech startup based on a charismatic founder's pitch, only to watch the company fold within seven months when it ran out of runway, leaving his salary unpaid for two months.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experience eroded his trust in authoritative figures and institutional promises, shifting him toward relying heavily on peer reviews and word-of-mouth from friends he trusts before making any significant financial or career commitment."
