                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:42:24.846207Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: During his first year of his postgraduate program, he bought a budget laptop to save money, which failed catastrophically two weeks before his thesis submission, forcing him to spend three frantic days recovering data from a repair shop in Koramangala. \u2014 This experience hardened his conviction that cutting costs on core tools is a false economy, cementing his quality_vs_budget tension and making him consistently prioritize durability over price even when his income is stretched.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:42:24.846207Z"
              },
              {
