                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:42:24.846219Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: He joined a Bengaluru fintech startup based on a charismatic founder's pitch, only to watch the company fold within seven months when it ran out of runway, leaving his salary unpaid for two months. \u2014 The experience eroded his trust in authoritative figures and institutional promises, shifting him toward relying heavily on peer reviews and word-of-mouth from friends he trusts before making any significant financial or career commitment.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:42:24.846219Z"
